<h2><a name="Tour highlights"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Tour highlights</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Spend a week discovering the culture and scenery of Norway</li>
<li>Enjoy a guided tour of the colourful city of Bergen</li>
<li>Journey on the scenic express boat down Norway's longest and deepest fjord: <span>Sognefjord</span></li>
<li>Take one of the world's best train journeys along the Flåm Railway</li>
<li>Revel in nature's beauty, taking in mountain views, waterfalls, fjords and glaciers</li>
<li>See the best of Oslo on a guided tour of the vibrant capital city </li>
<li>Visit the Northern Lights Xperium in Oslo </li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="hhttps://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-norway/bergen-to-oslo-fjord-experience#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Itinerary"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Itinerary</span></h2>
<p><strong>Day 1: UK to Bergen</strong></p>
<p>Land in Bergen and transfer to the city centre by shuttle bus. Spend the rest of the day exploring this vibrant city.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 2: Bergen</strong></p>
<p>Today will start with meeting your local guide and having a walking tour of Bergen. Visiting all the main attractions, including the UNESCO World Heritage listed Bryggen, Church of Mary and the famous fish market on the waterfront. Once you have seen all of those great sites, take the Fløibanen Funicular to the top of Mount Fløyen for fantastic views over the whole city and see the gateway to the Fjords. </p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 3: Bergen to Balestrand</strong></p>
<p>This morning you will take a scenic express boat down the Sognefjord, the longest and deepest Norwegian Fjord. Seeing small Norweigan towns and changes in the colourful fjord scenery along your way. After this scenic journey you will arrive in Balestrand.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 4: Balestrand</strong></p>
<p>Today is a day of leisure to discover the enchanting village of Balestrand at your own pace. Alternatively you can take the optional full day excursion to the idyllic village of Fjærland, which is 'where glacier meets the fjord', and its surrounding areas. Visiting two glaciers, Supphellebreen and Bøyabreen, and sailing through the beautiful Fjærland Fjord with its steep mountain and vibrant landscape.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 5:</strong><span> <strong>Balestrand to Oslo</strong></span></p>
<p>Continuing along the Sognefjord, the King of Norway, your cruise will arrive in the charming village of Flåm. Taking the famous Flåm Railway is definitely a highlight of this tour. You will pass the beautiful mountainous scenery with waterfalls to each side and travelling through 20 tunnels, on one of the steepest train-lines in the world! From the Flåm Railway you will swap to the great Bergen Railway to get you to the capital city of Oslo.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 6: Oslo</strong></p>
<p>After breakfast you will meet your guide for some city sightseeing. Receive great insight to the vibrant capital city and its highlights, from the Frogner Park to the Royal Palace and Akershus Fortress. Then its time to visit Xperium, a 15 minute standing attraction on a journey to discover the Northern Lights. Take the rest of the day to wander round the city and keep exploring! </p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 7: Oslo to UK</strong></p>
<p>Transfer to Oslo airport for your flight home.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-norway/bergen-to-oslo-fjord-experience#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Your holiday includes"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Your holiday includes</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Return flights from the UK</li>
<li>Return airport transfers (by Airport Shuttle, with the chance to upgrade to a private car)</li>
<li>Scenic rail transfer on the ‘Bergen Railway’ from Mydral to Oslo</li>
<li>Famous Fl<span>å</span>m Railway excursion </li>
<li>Northern Lights Xperium in Oslo</li>
<li>Sightseeing tour of Bergen and Oslo</li>
<li>Scenic coastal ferry cruise from Bergen to Balestrand</li>
<li>Accommodation with private facilities throughout</li>
<li>6 breakfasts, 2 dinners</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Your holiday excludes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Any extras, drinks, gratuities and personal expenses</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Optional Tour Activities </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Bergen Sightseeing Cruise with light dinner<span> </span><em>(Day 2 at 17:00, approx. 1.5 hours)</em></li>
<li>Bergen Food Tour<span> </span><em>(Day 2 at 15:00, approx. 3 hours)</em></li>
<li>Fjærland Full Day Tour<span> </span><em>(Day 4 - pre-booking is recommended)</em></li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-norway/bergen-to-oslo-fjord-experience#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
